cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on the field of machine learning, specifically on neural networks and their vulnerability to adversarial samples. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of evolutionary algorithms, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with the security aspect of neural networks, which could fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of image datasets such as MNIST and CIFAR-10 suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the relationship between the complexity of the model and the dataset, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
